Insight Builder Supported Functions

Before building your insight, review the supported functions.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Supported Functions

The lag and lead functions are supported only when you add an aggregate within an aggregate node of your insight.

AREA	INSIGHT BUILDER	SQL
Math and statistical	add, subtract, multiply, divide, avg, max, min, mean, sum, stddev, count (expr)	add, subtract, multiply, divide, avg, max, min, mean, sum, stddev, count (expr)
Logical operators	Logical not, Less than, Less than or equal to, Equal to, Greater than, Greater than or equal to, and, or, not if, in, distinct, like, isnull, ifnull, like, between	Logical not, Less than, Less than or equal to, Equal to, Greater than, Greater than or equal to, and, or, not if, in, distinct, like, isnull, ifnull, like, between
Date & time functions	cdphour, cdpday, cdpmonth, cdpquarter, cdpyear, hour, day, month, quarter, year, current_date(), date_sub, date_add, datediff, month_between, dayofweek, dayofmonth, to_date, to_timestamp, date_trunc	cdphour, cdpday, cdpmonth, cdpquarter, cdpyear, hour, day, month, quarter, year, current_date(), date_sub, date_add, datediff, month_between, dayofweek, dayofmonth, to_date, to_timestamp, date_trunc
Transforms	substring, abs, rtrim, log, rand, round, exp, greatest, least	substring, abs, rtrim, log, rand, round, exp, greatest, least
Analytical functions	lead, lag, ntile, rank, dense_rank, percent_rank, row_number, limit, CASE, approx. count distinct, first, last	lead, lag, ntile, rank, dense_rank, percent_rank, row_number, limit, CASE, approx. count distinct, first, last
Metrics on metrics	Supported	Supported
Streaming insights	Supported	Supported
Clone	Not supported	Supported
Join	Supported	Supported
Filters	Supported	Supported
Aggregation	Supported	Supported
Subquery	Not supported	Supported
Advanced functions (Rank, NTILE, APPROX, DISTINCT COUNT, Case statements)	Supported	Supported
IN operator	Not supported	Supported
Aggregate Functions in Insight Builder
The aggregate function performs a calculation on a set of values in Data Cloud and returns a single value.
Filters in Insight Builder
The filters in the Visual builder are similar to the “Where” clause in the standard SQL. You can define filters on the measures and dimensions.
